title: In South Korea, Week of Mourning Follows Halloween Crowd Crush
description: South Koreans are trying to come to grips with a tragedy that claimed the lives of 156 people, many of them young.

title: Pakistan Ex-Prime Minister Imran Khan Shot in Leg at Protest Rally
description: Video footage shows Khan being carried away from the scene with a bandage on his leg

title: A Biden-Xi Summit Presents Latest Challenge to U.S.-China Ties
description: U.S. and Chinese officials are wrangling over whether the two presidents will meet around the Group of 20 summit in mid-November in an effort to prevent strained relations from deteriorating further.

title: Bank of England Raises Key Interest Rate by 0.75 Point
description: The hike is the largest since 1989, as the bank fights a surge in inflation from rising energy prices even as the U.K. economy slides into an expected recession.

title: Russian Shelling Forces Ukraine Nuclear Plant to Run on Backup Generators
description: Moscow resumed attacks on energy infrastructure overnight and Kyiv said the Zaporizhzhia nuclear-power facility had 15 days’ worth of fuel left to run generators.

title: Israel's Netanyahu Edges Closer to Election Win
description: With 93% of votes counted, Israel’s former prime minister appears set to return to power after more than a year in the opposition.

title: North Korea Fires Three Missiles, Including ICBM
description: The activity came a day after the Kim Jong Un regime launched nearly two dozen missiles off its eastern and western coasts.
